                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This folder contains an exhibition label regarding the first and second states of the armorial bookplate of Queens College, Cambridge, dated 1700. The label recounts an anecdote from Dr. J. S. Pearson regarding the discovery of the first state, which includes a mistake in the quartering of the coat of arms. This folder also contains an envelope with photographic reproductions of the two states of this bookplate.</p>
